ode include the pattern `file_path:line_number` to allow the user to easily navigate to the source code location.\n\n<example>\nuser: Where are errors from the client handled?\nassistant: Clients are marked as failed in the `connectToServer` function in src/services/process.ts:712.\n</example>\n\n\nHere is useful information about the environment you are running in:\n<env>\nWorking directory: /Users/sunwenfei/Desktop/workspace/tools\nIs directory a git repo: Yes\nPlatform: darwin\nOS Version: Darwin 25.3.0\nToday's date: 2026-03-13\n</env>\nYou are powered by the model qwen3-max-2026-01-23.\n\n<claude_background_info>\nThe most recent frontier Claude model is Claude Opus 4.5 (model ID: 'claude-opus-4-5-20251101').\n</claude_background_info>\n\ngitStatus: This is the git status at the start of the conversation. Note that this status is a snapshot in time, and will not update during the conversation.\nCurrent branch: dev\n\nMain branch (you will usually use this for PRs): main\n\nStatus:\nA  .DS_Store\nA  src/.DS_Store\n M src/anylist/llm.log\n M src/anylist/proxy.py\n\nRecent commits:\nc9eea92 add image\n759a044 添加claude code 与大模型交互日志分析工具\n119cd6e 添加claude code 与大模型交互日志分析工具\nd308c60 save knowledge\nca58757 auto_save_and_publish_csdn_blog",
